1 A. PERIODICAL PERMIT NEWSPAPER: A legal newspaper of the
2 county is any newspaper of general circulation which, during a
3 period of one hundred four (104) consecutive weeks immediately prior
4 to the first publication of such notice, advertisement, or
5 publication:
6 1. has maintained a paid general subscription circulation in
7 the county; and
8 2. has been admitted to the United States mails as paid second-
9 class general periodical mail matter; and
10 3. has been continuously and uninterruptedly published in the
11 county.
12 B. NONPERIODICAL PERMIT NEWSPAPER: A legal newspaper of the
13 county is any newspaper of general circulation which, during a
14 period of one hundred four (104) consecutive weeks immediately prior
15 to the first publication of such notice, advertisement or
16 publication:
17 1. Has published a printed issue at least once per week;
18 2. Continuously offers paid subscriptions to the general public
19 and maintains a minimum of two hundred (200) paid print
20 subscriptions to individual verified subscribers, and delivers such
21 subscriptions by verified mail or carrier delivery to paid
22 individual subscribers. The cost of a paid subscription shall
23 exceed a nominal fee including the cost of printing and
24 distribution;
